                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">632.6231/174: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-17T13:00:00-03:00"
                            >June 17, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 17—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. My telegram No. 59, June 4, noon. The Brazilian-German compensation
                    arrangement was officially extended for a period of 3 <pb facs="0344" n="334"
                        xml:id="pg_334"/> months by notes exchanged yesterday between the Minister
                    of Foreign Affairs and the German Ambassador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
